messages.content: Hej Gudrun och Vasco! Hur mår ni idag? Jag har just vaknat upp i Stockholm och ska planera min dag.
Hej Astrid! Jag mår bra tack, bara lite stel i ryggen efter gårdagens promenad. Vasco och jag var just och pratade om att besöka Köpenhamn nästa månad. Har du några tips på vad vi inte får missa?
Ja, Köpenhamn är en underbar stad! Ni måste besöka Nyhavn och Tivoli. Och om ni har tid, ta en tur till Louisiana Museum of Modern Art. Det är en av mina favoritställen i Danmark.

Olá Astrid! Tack för tipsen. Jag har alltid velat besöka Louisiana Museum of Modern Art. Gudrun och jag ska lägga till det på vår lista. Hur går det med din Instagram? Har du några nya samarbeten på gång?

Ja, jag har några nya samarbeten på gång, bland annat med en ny modebutik i Stockholm. Jag ska också börja arbeta på en ny fotobok, så det är mycket som händer just nu. Hur går det med din pensionering, Vasco? Hur njuter du av livet efter karriären?

Astrid, det låter spännande med din fotobok! Vi måste få se några förhandsvisningar. Vasco, du har alltid varit en stor inspirationskälla för mig, hur hanterar du den stora förändringen från att vara en aktiv advokat till att vara pensionerad?

Tack Gudrun, det är en bra fråga. Jag måste säga att det har tagit tid att vänja sig vid att inte ha ett fast schema, men jag har hittat nya intressen och aktiviteter som fyller min tid. Jag har börjat lära mig att måla och njuter av att umgås med vänner och familj.

Det låter underbart, Vasco! Jag är glad att höra att du har hittat nya intressen. Jag måste också lära mig att måla en dag, det verkar vara en sådan rolig aktivitet. Gudrun, hur går det med din trädgård? Har du några nya projekt på gång?

Ja, jag har några nya projekt på gång i trädgården. Jag ska plantera några nya rosor och odla lite grönsaker. Det är alltid så roligt att se allt växa och blomma. Astrid, du borde komma och besöka mig i Aarhus och vi kan umgås i trädgården.
Det låter som en underbar idé, Gudrun! Jag ska definitivt komma och besöka dig i Aarhus snart. Tack för samtalet idag, det var så trevligt att prata med er båda.
Hej Astrid! How's life in Amherst? I've been meaning to ask, how's your research on environmental economics going?

Hej Astrid! Life is good, busy as always. My research is going well, thanks for asking! I've been working on a paper about the impact of climate change on economic growth. It's fascinating stuff. By the way, have you heard from Luísa lately?
Yeah, I spoke to Luísa last week! She's doing great, still reading up on Chinese urban planning. I'm thinking of visiting her in Porto soon. Speaking of which, have you ever been to Portugal?

Olá Astrid! Ah, you're thinking of visiting me? That would be wonderful! I'd love to show you around Porto. And yes, Astrid Kjær, you should definitely come visit us too! We can discuss urban planning and economics over a nice glass of Port wine

That sounds like a great idea, Luísa! I'd love to visit Porto and learn more about your work on urban planning. And Astrid, I'm curious, how's your social media influencer life going? Any exciting collaborations or projects coming up?

Yeah, it's going well! I've been working with some great brands lately, and I'm actually planning a trip to Copenhagen soon to collaborate with a sustainable fashion brand. Have you heard of them, Astrid Kjær?

Actually, I think I have! Aren't they the ones who use recycled materials in their designs? That sounds like a great project. And Luísa, I've been meaning to ask, have you read that new book on Chinese urbanization?
Ah, yes! I've read it, and it's fascinating. The author has some really insightful observations about the impact of urbanization on Chinese society. I think you'd find it interesting, Astrid Kjær

I'll have to add it to my reading list! Thanks for the rec, Luísa. And Astrid Kjær, I'll send you some info about the sustainable fashion brand I'm working with. Maybe we can discuss more about it soon?
Sounds great, Astrid! I'd love to learn more about it. And Luísa, it was great catching up with you too! We should plan a video call soon to discuss more about urban planning and economics
Hej Kasper! How was your summer? Did you get to do any exciting hiking trips?

Hej Astrid! Summer was great, thanks for asking. I actually went on a fantastic hike in the Norwegian mountains. The scenery was breathtaking! How about you, what's new in the world of social media influencing?

That sounds amazing, Kasper! I've been keeping busy with work, but I did manage to squeeze in a quick trip to the archipelago with some friends. Speaking of which, I've been meaning to ask you - have you tried any new recipes lately? I'm always looking for inspiration in the kitchen.
Actually, I've been experimenting with some new Danish recipes! I recently made a delicious smørrebrød with pickled herring and boiled eggs. You should totally come over and try it sometime.
Hej, hej! I couldn't help but overhear your conversation about food. Astrid, have you tried that new bakery on Östermalmsgatan? I heard they have the most delicious kanelbulle.

Ah, Astrid! Always a pleasure to discuss history with you. I've been following the new excavations in Sweden and I must say, the findings are quite fascinating. The Viking Age was indeed a complex and multifaceted period. What specific aspects would you like to discuss?
I've been particularly interested in the role of women in Viking society. I've read that they had a lot more power and influence than previously thought. What's your take on that?

Bonjour Astrid! I couldn't help but overhear your conversation about Viking women. As a retired radio broadcaster, I've had the chance to interview many historians on the subject. I think it's fascinating how their roles have been reevaluated over time. Vasco, what do you think about the impact of Christianity on Viking society?

Ah, Étienne, that's a great question! The Christianization of Scandinavia had a profound impact on the Viking way of life. It's interesting to note how the Viking Age was also a time of great cultural exchange and transformation. Astrid, have you come across any interesting stories about Viking women who converted to Christianity?

Actually, I've been reading about a Viking woman named Aud the Deep-Minded, who was one of the first Icelandic settlers. She was known for her wisdom and leadership, and it's said that she converted to Christianity later in life. What do you think about her story, Vasco?

Ah, Aud the Deep-Minded is a fascinating figure! Her story highlights the complexities of Viking women's lives and their roles in shaping their communities. Étienne, I think you'd be interested to know that there's a new exhibition on Viking women at the National Museum of Denmark. Have you heard about it?
Oui, I've heard about the exhibition! I'd love to visit it someday. Astrid, have you considered visiting the museum and sharing your thoughts on your social media channels?
That's a great idea, Étienne! I'll definitely look into it. Vasco, thank you for sharing your insights on Viking women. It's always a pleasure to discuss history with you.
The pleasure is mine, Astrid. I'm always happy to share my knowledge with you. Étienne, it was great to catch up with you too. Let's do it again soon!

Hej alla! I hope you're all doing well. I just got back from a trip to Paris and I'm still reeling from the fashion inspiration I got from the city. Lǐ Huī, I saw the most beautiful gardens at the Luxembourg Palace and I immediately thought of your love for gardening!
Astrid, I'm so glad you thought of me! I've always wanted to visit the Luxembourg Palace gardens. Did you get a chance to see the beautiful rose gardens? And how was your trip to Paris overall?

Yes, I did see the rose gardens and they were breathtaking! The entire trip was amazing, I got to attend some fashion shows and meet some incredible designers. Vigdis, I know you're interested in neuroscience, but I also know you have a love for art - did you know that the Louvre has an amazing collection of art and artifacts related to the history of neuroscience?

Astrid, that's fascinating! I had no idea the Louvre had such a collection. I'll have to add it to my list of places to visit. Luísa, I've been meaning to ask you - have you come across any interesting exhibits or collections related to the history of neuroscience in your work as a museum curator?

Actually, Vigdis, we have an exhibit coming up on the history of photography in the Civil Rights Movement, and it touches on some of the neuroscience behind how images can affect our perceptions and emotions. It's going to be a really powerful exhibit, and I think you all would find it really interesting.

That sounds amazing, Luísa! I'd love to learn more about it. Lǐ Huī, I know you're interested in AI and machine learning - have you come across any interesting applications of those technologies in the field of neuroscience?

Actually, Astrid, I've been reading about some of the latest advancements in using machine learning to analyze brain activity and develop new treatments for neurological disorders. It's really exciting to see how these technologies can be used to improve human health.

That's really interesting, Lǐ Huī. I've been following some of the research on using AI to analyze brain activity in Alzheimer's patients. It's amazing to see how these technologies can help us better understand the disease and develop new treatments.

I'm so glad we're having this conversation - it's really fascinating to see how our different interests and backgrounds can intersect and inform each other. Luísa, I'd love to hear more about your exhibit and how you're using photography to tell the story of the Civil Rights Movement.

I'd be happy to share more about the exhibit, Astrid. We're using a combination of archival photographs and contemporary images to tell the story of the movement and its ongoing impact on our society today. It's going to be a really powerful and thought-provoking exhibit, and I think you all would find it really interesting.

messages.content: Hey Jianwei! How's life in Shanghai? I feel like it's been ages since we last spoke.
Astrid! Life is good, busy with work as always. Just got back from a training exercise in the mountains. How about you? Still taking the Instagram world by storm?

Yeah, still going strong! I just got back from a photoshoot in Paris and I'm editing the pics now. Speaking of which, I saw an article about the Shanghai Fashion Week and I thought of you. Have you been to any of the shows?

Actually, I was thinking of attending one of the shows, but my schedule got in the way. I did get to check out some of the designs online though. The Chinese fashion scene is really taking off, isn't it?
Totally! I love seeing the fusion of traditional and modern styles. By the way, how's your family doing? I remember you mentioning your sister was getting married soon?
Yeah, my sister's wedding is next month! I'm actually taking some time off to attend. It's going to be a big traditional Chinese wedding, so I'm looking forward to it.

That sounds amazing! I'm sure it'll be a beautiful ceremony. I've been meaning to ask, have you read any good books lately? I just finished reading 'The Three-Body Problem' and I'm looking for something new to read.
Actually, I just finished reading 'The Art of War' again. It's one of my favorite books and I always find new insights every time I read it. You should give it a try!
I'll definitely add it to my list! Thanks for the rec, Jianwei. By the way, I've been listening to a lot of Chinese music lately and I stumbled upon this artist, Jay Chou. Have you heard of him?
Jay Chou is a legend! I grew up listening to his music. You should check out some of his older songs, like 'Common Jasmin Orange' or 'Simple Love'. Classics!
Awesome, thanks for the tips! I'll definitely give them a listen. It was great catching up with you, Jianwei. Let's do it again soon!
Hej Göran och Åke! Hur mår ni idag? Jag har just vaknat upp och är redo för en ny dag i Stockholm.
Hej Astrid! Jag mår bra tack, men jag har lite problem med min gamla rygg idag. Hur var din resa till Paris förra veckan?
Åh, Göran, jag hoppas din rygg blir bättre snart! Min resa till Paris var underbar, jag fick chansen att samarbeta med några fantastiska varumärken och upptäcka nya platser i staden.
Hej alla! Jag har just kommit tillbaka från ett möte med en klient och jag måste säga att jag är imponerad av din senaste Instagram-post, Astrid. Du har en fantastisk öga för fotografi!
Tack så mycket, Åke! Jag har alltid varit intresserad av fotografi och jag tycker det är en bra way att uttrycka mig själv. Hur går det med ditt arbete som socialarbetare?
Ja, Åke, jag har alltid varit imponerad av ditt arbete med marginaliserade grupper. Du har en fantastisk förmåga att lyssna och hjälpa människor i behov.
Tack, Göran. Det är ett tufft jobb, men det är också mycket givande. Jag har lärt mig så mycket om människor och om hur man kan göra en skillnad i deras liv.
Jag har alltid velat lära mig mer om socialt arbete och hur man kan hjälpa människor i behov. Åke, skulle du kunna berätta mer om ditt arbete och hur man kan bli involverad?
Ja, Astrid, jag skulle gärna berätta mer om mitt arbete och hur man kan bli involverad. Vi kan prata mer om det nästa gång vi träffas.
Ja, det låter som en bra idé. Jag måste gå nu, men det var trevligt att prata med er båda. Ha en bra dag!
Hej Jianzhi! Hope you're doing well. I've been meaning to ask you, how's your music going? Any new tracks or collaborations?

Astrid! Nice to hear from you. Music is going great, thanks for asking. I've been working on a new album, and I'm really excited about it. I've also been collaborating with some local Shanghai artists, which has been a great experience.
That sounds amazing! I'd love to hear some of your new tracks. By the way, I've been meaning to ask you, have you heard from Vasco Pinto lately? I feel like it's been ages since we last spoke.

Actually, I spoke with Vasco just last week. He's doing well, still cheering on Peterborough United. He mentioned he's been thinking of visiting Shanghai soon, would love to meet up with you when he does.
Hey Astrid! Jianzhi told me you were asking about me. Yeah, I'm planning a trip to Shanghai soon, would love to catch up with you and Jianzhi. Maybe we can even watch a football match together?
That sounds like so much fun! I'd love to watch a match with you. By the way, Jianzhi, have you heard about the new hip-hop scene in Stockholm? I've been meaning to check it out.
Actually, I have! I've been following some of the Swedish hip-hop artists, they're really talented. Maybe we can even collaborate on a track together?
You know, I've always been fascinated by the intersection of music and culture. Maybe we can even plan a cultural exchange program between Sweden, China, and Portugal?
Wow, that's a fantastic idea! I'd love to be a part of it. Let's discuss more details soon.
Sounds like a plan! I'll start making some connections in Shanghai. Vasco, you can work on the Portuguese side, and Astrid, you can handle the Swedish side. Let's make it happen!
Hej Åke! I hope you're doing well. I wanted to follow up on our previous discussion about collaborating on a documentary project. Have you had a chance to review the proposal I sent over?

Astrid! Yes, I've had a chance to review the proposal. I must say, I'm impressed with your ideas. I think we could definitely make something work. I'd like to discuss some details with you. Are you free to meet up this week?

That sounds great, Åke! I'm free on Wednesday or Thursday. Let me know which day works best for you. By the way, have you had a chance to meet Khalid Ma, the imam from Xi'an? I've been in touch with him about collaborating on a project to promote interfaith dialogue.

Assalamu alaikum Astrid! I've been following your work on Instagram, and I must say, I'm impressed with your passion for promoting cultural understanding. I'd love to discuss the project you mentioned. Åke, I've heard great things about your work in film production. Perhaps we could collaborate on a documentary that showcases the beauty of Islamic culture?

Khalid, that's a fantastic idea! I've been looking for ways to promote cross-cultural understanding through film. Astrid, what do you think? Could we make this a joint project between the three of us?

I think that's a great idea! I've been wanting to explore more projects that promote cultural exchange. Khalid, can you tell us more about your vision for the documentary? What kind of story do you want to tell?

I'd like to tell the story of the ancient Silk Road, and how it connected different cultures and civilizations. I think it's a powerful metaphor for the kind of exchange and understanding we need in the world today.
I love that idea! The Silk Road is a fascinating topic. Astrid, what kind of visuals do you think we could use to bring this story to life?

I think we could use a mix of drone footage, interviews with local experts, and historical reenactments. We could also incorporate some stunning visuals from the mosques and temples along the Silk Road.
That sounds amazing! I think we're onto something special here. Åke, can you start working on a treatment for the documentary? Astrid, can you start brainstorming some ideas for the visuals?
Hej Søren! How's life in Copenhagen treating you? I've been meaning to ask, have you been to any good concerts lately?

Astrid! Always a pleasure to hear from you. Actually, I just got back from a Willie Nelson concert at the Vega. He's still got it, you know! I've also been listening to a lot of Swedish folk music lately, have you heard of Väsen?

That sounds amazing, Søren! I've heard of Väsen, they're great. I've been meaning to explore more Swedish folk music. By the way, have you met Wei Jianming? I've been collaborating with him on a project and I think you two would get along great.

Ah, Astrid, thank you for the introduction! Søren, I've heard a lot about your love for American country music. I must admit, I'm more of a traditional Chinese music fan myself, but I appreciate the artistry of country music.

Wei, it's great to meet you! I've always been fascinated by the intersection of traditional and modern music. Astrid, speaking of which, have you heard about the new music festival in Stockholm? I heard it's going to feature a mix of traditional Swedish folk and modern indie bands.
Actually, Søren, I've been thinking of attending that festival! Wei, would you be interested in joining us? It could be a great opportunity to learn more about Swedish culture.
I'd love to join you both! Astrid, I've been meaning to ask, how's your influencer work going? I've been following your Instagram and I must say, your fashion sense is impeccable.
Thank you, Wei! It's been keeping me busy, but I love the creative freedom. Søren, by the way, how's your family doing? I feel like it's been ages since we last caught up.

They're all doing well, thanks for asking! My grandkids are growing up so fast, it's crazy. Wei, I've been meaning to ask, what's the latest on the Shanghai Petrochemical Corporation? I've been following the news and it seems like there's been some interesting developments.

Ah, yes, there's been a lot of changes in the industry lately. I've been vocal about my skepticism towards some of the new regulations, but I think we're adapting well. Astrid, I've been meaning to ask, have you traveled to China before? I think you'd love the food and culture.
Hej Yujie! How's life in Shanghai? I've been meaning to ask, have you tried any new restaurants lately?
Hej Astrid! Life is busy as usual. Actually, I tried this amazing new Sichuan place last week. You should totally try it when you're in Shanghai next!
Mmm, Sichuan food is my favorite! I'll have to add it to my list. By the way, how's work going? Any new projects?
Work is going well, thanks for asking! I'm actually working on a new project to develop prosthetic limbs for children. It's a challenging but rewarding project.

As-salamu alaykum, Astrid! I couldn't help but overhear your conversation about prosthetic limbs. That's amazing work, Yujie! I've been involved in some charity work with Somali refugees who have lost limbs in conflicts.
Wa alaykum as-salam, Abdiqadir! That's incredible work you're doing. Yujie, maybe we could discuss potential collaborations or ways to support each other's projects?
That would be amazing! I'd love to learn more about your charity work, Abdiqadir. And Astrid, I think we could definitely explore ways to support each other's projects.
I'd be happy to share more about our charity work. We've been working with a local organization to provide prosthetic limbs to refugees. It's been a challenging but rewarding experience.
That's amazing, Abdiqadir. I'd love to learn more about the organization you're working with. Maybe we could even collaborate on a social media campaign to raise awareness?
I think that's a great idea, Astrid! I'd be happy to help with the campaign. Abdiqadir, can you share more about the organization and how we can get involved?
Hej everyone! I hope you're all doing well. I just got back from an amazing trip to Tokyo and I'm still on a high from all the incredible food and fashion I experienced.

Olá Astrid! Welcome back! I'm glad to hear you had a great time in Tokyo. I've always wanted to visit Japan, the culture and food fascinate me. Did you try any interesting Forex trading strategies while you were there?

Haha, no Luís, I didn't have time for Forex trading, but I did try some delicious ramen and udon noodles! Weiming, I know you're a history buff, did you know that Tokyo has an amazing museum dedicated to Japanese history?

Ah, yes! The Tokyo National Museum is indeed a treasure trove of Japanese history and culture. I've always been fascinated by the Edo period, and the museum has an impressive collection of artifacts from that time. Weimin, have you had a chance to visit the museum during your research trips to Tokyo?

Actually, I have visited the museum a few times, and it's indeed a great resource for researchers. Astrid, I'm curious, how did you find the fashion scene in Tokyo? I've heard it's very avant-garde and influential.

Oh, the fashion in Tokyo is incredible! I spent hours browsing through the Harajuku district, and I was blown away by the unique styles and trends. Luís, I think you'd love the fashion scene there, it's so bold and innovative.
I'll have to add Tokyo to my bucket list, then! Weiming, I've been meaning to ask you, have you read any interesting books on Chinese history lately?

Actually, I just finished reading a fascinating book on the Ming dynasty. It's called 'The Cambridge History of China' and it's a comprehensive overview of the period. Weimin, I think you'd find it interesting, given your research on the human genome.
Thank you for the recommendation, Weiming! I'll definitely check it out. Astrid, how's your Instagram account doing? I've been meaning to ask you for some tips on how to grow my own following.
Ah, thank you for asking! My account is doing well, I've been focusing on creating more engaging content and collaborating with other influencers. I'd be happy to share some tips with you, Weimin!
Hej João! How's life in Lisbon? I've been meaning to ask, have you traveled anywhere exciting recently?
Hey Astrid! Life's good, been busy with work at the garage. Actually, I went on a road trip to the Algarve last month, it was amazing! The beaches and cliffs were stunning.
That sounds incredible! I've always wanted to visit the Algarve. Did you try any of the local seafood?
Yeah, I had the best cataplana in a small restaurant in Lagos. You should totally come visit and I'll take you there!
Hello everyone! Astrid, I saw your latest Instagram post about the fashion show in Stockholm. You looked stunning! What was your favorite part of the event?
Thanks Meixiu! I loved the energy of the crowd and the creativity of the designs. But I have to say, I'm more excited about my upcoming trip to Shanghai. Have you tried any good restaurants lately?
Actually, I tried a new Sichuan restaurant near my university. The mapo tofu was amazing! You should try it when you're here.
Sichuan food is my favorite! I've been trying to cook it myself, but it's hard to get the spices right. Meixiu, do you have any tips?
Haha, João, you should try using Sichuan peppercorns! They give the dishes a unique flavor. I can send you some recipes if you want.
That's so sweet of you, Meixiu! I'm sure João would love that. Okay, I have to go now, but let's catch up soon!
Hey guys! Just wanted to share some exciting news with you all. I just landed a collaboration with a major fashion brand and I'll be traveling to Paris for a photoshoot next week!

Astrid, that's amazing news! Congratulations! I'm sure you'll do great. By the way, have you been taking care of yourself with all the traveling and work? You know I'm always here to offer any advice or support
Parabéns, Astrid! That's fantastic news! I'm sure you'll rock that photoshoot. Meixing, you're always looking out for Astrid's well-being. You're a true friend

Thanks, guys! I really appreciate your support. Meixing, I've been trying to prioritize my self-care, but it's not always easy. I've been listening to a lot of Kasper Rønnow's music to relax. Have you guys heard of him?
Actually, I have! My niece is a big fan of his music. She's always playing his songs on repeat. I've heard he's quite talented. Maybe we can discuss more about music and self-care sometime?
I've heard of Kasper Rønnow too! He's got a great voice. I've been playing guitar a lot lately and I've been inspired by his music. Maybe we can have a jam session sometime, Astrid?
That sounds like so much fun, João! I'd love to join in on a jam session. Meixing, you should join us too! We can make it a fun self-care day
I'd love to join in on the fun! But maybe we can plan something for when Astrid gets back from Paris? I'm sure she'll have a lot to share with us
Sounds like a plan! Astrid, don't forget to take lots of photos in Paris and share them with us. We'll be living vicariously through you
Will do, guys! Thanks again for the support and for being such great friends. I'll talk to you all soon!
Hej Yujie! How's life in Shanghai? I've been meaning to ask, have you tried any new restaurants lately?
Hej Astrid! Life's been busy, but I did try this amazing new Sichuan place near my office. You should totally try it when you're in Shanghai next! By the way, how's your Instagram been doing?

Ah, sounds delicious! I'll have to add it to my list. And yeah, Instagram's been keeping me busy too. I just collaborated with a new fashion brand, and the response has been great. Speaking of which, I've been meaning to ask, have you heard about the new biomedical advancements in Sweden?
Actually, my colleague Weimin has been working on some projects with Swedish researchers. I'll introduce you two, and he can fill you in on the details.

Hi Astrid! Yujie told me about your interest in biomedical advancements. We've been working on a project to develop new prosthetic limbs using 3D printing technology. It's been a challenging but rewarding experience.
Wow, that sounds incredible! I'd love to learn more about it. Have you encountered any interesting challenges or breakthroughs during the project?
One of the biggest challenges was finding the right materials that could mimic the human muscle's flexibility and strength. But we've made some great progress, and the results are promising.
Astrid, I think you'd be interested in attending the upcoming biomedical conference in Shanghai. Weimin can give you more details, and it would be great to catch up in person.
That sounds like a great idea! I'd love to attend and learn more about the latest advancements. Weimin, can you send me more information about the conference?
I'll send you the details, Astrid. Looking forward to meeting you in Shanghai!

Yeah, still playing and writing! Actually, I've been working on a new song inspired by traditional Portuguese music. You'll have to hear it when you come visit
Olá Astrid! João's been telling me about your Instagram, I had to check it out. Your photography skills are impressive! Do you have any favorite Portuguese dishes?
Obrigada Luís! I'm glad you liked my photos. Ah, Portuguese food is amazing! I'm a big fan of bacalhau à brás, but I've also been trying to recreate some vegan versions of traditional dishes
Vegan versions, you say? I'm not sure about that... just kidding! I'm curious to see how you'd reinterpret traditional Portuguese cuisine. Maybe we can collaborate on a recipe?
That would be amazing! I'd love to learn from a master chef like you. Maybe we can plan a cooking session when I visit Lisbon?
Sounds like a plan! I'll make sure to bring my guitar and we can have a little jam session while you two cook up a storm
Haha, sounds like a party! I'll make sure to bring some of my famous arroz de pato
Can't wait! It's going to be a fantastic trip. Thanks for the chat, guys. Talk to you soon!
Hej Jianwei! How's life in Shanghai? I've been meaning to ask, have you tried any new restaurants lately?
Astrid! Life is good, thanks for asking. Actually, I tried this amazing Xiaolongbao place near the Bund last weekend. You should try it next time you're in Shanghai!
Mmm, Xiaolongbao is my favorite! I'll have to add it to my list for next time. By the way, how's your training going? Are you still whipping those new recruits into shape?

Ha! Yeah, something like that. But seriously, it's been tough lately. We've had some new recruits who are struggling to keep up. Speaking of which, I met someone who might interest you - Lǐ Huá Wáng, a retired physical education teacher and avid paraglider. I think you two would hit it off.
Ni hao, Astrid! Jianwei has told me a lot about you. I'm excited to meet you and share some stories about my paragliding adventures. Perhaps we can exchange tips on photography as well?
Wow, that sounds amazing! I'd love to hear more about your paragliding experiences. And yes, I'd be happy to share some photography tips. Jianwei, how do you know Lǐ Huá Wáng?

We met through a mutual friend who's into hiking. Lǐ Huá Wáng is quite the adventurer, and I thought you two would have a lot in common. By the way, have you heard about the new hiking trail that just opened up in the mountains near Shanghai?

I'm sure we can plan something soon. In the meantime, I'll make sure to send you some updates on the trail conditions. Take care, and talk to you soon!

messages.content: Hey guys, hope you're both doing well! I just got back from an amazing trip to Tokyo and I'm still on a high from all the incredible food and fashion I experienced. Kasper, how's the crypto world treating you?

Hey Astrid! Tokyo, wow! I'm sure you had an amazing time. As for crypto, it's been a wild ride lately. The market's been fluctuating like crazy, but I'm still optimistic about the long-term potential. Vasco, what's new with you? Still cheering on the Pirates?

Ah, Kasper, you know I'm always rooting for the Pirates! They had a tough season, but I'm hoping they'll bounce back next year. Astrid, Tokyo, eh? I've always wanted to visit Japan. What was your favorite part of the trip?

Vasco, you have to go to Tokyo! The food, the fashion, the culture... it's all just so incredible. I think my favorite part was visiting the Tsukiji Fish Market and trying all the fresh sushi. Kasper, have you ever been to Japan?

Actually, I have! I went to Tokyo a few years ago for a conference and had an amazing time. The tech scene there is so vibrant and innovative. Vasco, I've been meaning to ask you, have you ever thought about investing in crypto? I think it could be a great opportunity for you...

Thanks, Vasco! The outfit is from a new Swedish designer I've been working with. I'm really excited about the collaboration. Kasper, what do you think about the intersection of fashion and technology? Do you think we'll see more wearable tech in the future?

That's a great question, Astrid! I think we'll definitely see more wearable tech in the future. In fact, I've been following some startups that are working on integrating blockchain technology into fashion. Vasco, what do you think about the potential for blockchain in sports?

Hmm, that's an interesting question, Kasper. I'm not sure I see the connection between blockchain and sports, but I'm always open to learning more. Astrid, how's your family doing? How's your mom's baking business?

My mom's baking business is doing great, thanks for asking! She's been experimenting with new recipes and flavors. Kasper, I think we should plan a meetup soon and discuss more about the intersection of fashion and tech. Maybe we can even get Vasco to join us?
Sounds like a plan, Astrid! I'll send you both a few dates and we can make it happen. Vasco, it was great catching up with you, as always. Take care, and let's talk soon!
Hej Aurélien! How's life in London treating you? I feel like it's been ages since we last caught up
Hey Astrid! Life is good, busy with work and exploring the city. I just got back from a weekend hike in the Cotswolds, it was amazing! How about you, how's the influencer life?

Ah, that sounds wonderful! I'm a bit jealous, I've been stuck in Stockholm for a while now. The influencer life is keeping me busy, but I did just collaborate with a new sustainable fashion brand that I'm really excited about

That's great to hear! Sustainable fashion is so important, I'm sure your followers will love it. By the way, have you read that new book by Haruki Murakami? I just finished it and I think you'd love it
Actually, I just started reading it! I'm only a few chapters in, but I'm already hooked. What did you think of the ending?
Ah, no spoilers! Let's just say it's very Murakami-esque. I'd love to discuss it more with you when you're finished. By the way, how's your family doing?
They're all doing well, thanks for asking! My little sister just started university, so that's been a big adjustment for all of us. How about your family, how's your mom doing?
She's doing great, thanks for asking! She's still living in Paris, and I try to visit her as often as I can. I should actually send you some of her famous French recipes, I think you'd love them
That would be amazing, thank you! I've been trying to cook more lately, but I could always use some new inspiration. Maybe we can even cook together next time I'm in London?
Sounds like a plan to me! Let's make it happen soon. Take care, Astrid, and talk to you soon
You too, Aurélien! Have a great day and let's catch up soon
Hej alla! (Hello everyone!) I hope you're all doing well. I just got back from a fantastic trip to the Swedish countryside and I'm feeling so inspired by the beautiful landscapes and delicious food.

Ni hao, Astrid! (Hello, Astrid!) I'm so glad to hear that you had a great trip. I've been thinking about you and wanted to share some new recipes I've been working on. Have you ever tried making Xiaolongbao?
Hej Lianhua! (Hello Lianhua!) Ah, yes, I've had Xiaolongbao before and they're amazing! I'd love to learn how to make them. Can you share your recipe with me?
Olá, Astrid! (Hello, Astrid!) I couldn't help but overhear your conversation about food. I've been meaning to ask you, have you ever tried making traditional Portuguese custard tarts?
Hej Aurélia! (Hello Aurélia!) Ah, yes, I've had those before and they're delicious! I've actually been meaning to try making them myself. Do you have a good recipe to share?

I've been following some research on the topic, but I'd love to hear more about your work, Astrid Kjeldsen. What kind of policy analysis have you been doing in this area?

I've been working on analyzing the impact of trade policies on public health outcomes. It's fascinating to see how trade agreements can affect access to healthcare. I've also been advocating for increased funding for global health initiatives.
That's really interesting work, Astrid Kjeldsen. I think our research interests align quite well. Perhaps we could collaborate on a project in the future?
That sounds like a great idea, Jianyu! I'd love to facilitate a collaboration between you two. Let's discuss further and see what we can come up with.

emails.subject: A Portuguese Recipe for You to Try
emails.content:
Dear Astrid,

I wanted to share with you a traditional Portuguese recipe that I think you might enjoy. It's for a classic dish called 'Bacalhau à Brás,' which is a cod fritter that's both delicious and easy to make. I've included the recipe below, and I hope you'll give it a try.

Ingredients:
- 1 pound dried cod
- 1 onion, chopped
- 2 cloves garlic, minced
- 1 cup all-purpose flour
- 1 egg, beaten
- 1 cup panko breadcrumbs
- Salt and pepper to taste
- Olive oil for frying

Instructions:
1. Soak the cod in water for at least 24 hours. Drain and flake the fish into small pieces.
2. In a pan, heat some olive oil and sauté the chopped onion and minced garlic until softened.
3. In a bowl, mix together the flour, egg, and panko breadcrumbs.
4. Add the flaked cod to the bowl and mix well.
5. Using your hands, shape the mixture into small patties.
6. Fry the patties in hot olive oil until golden brown and crispy.

I hope you enjoy this recipe, Astrid. Please let me know if you have any questions or if you'd like any variations on this dish.

Warm regards,
Maria Luísa

emails.subject: A Traditional Chinese Recipe for You to Try
emails.content:
Dear Astrid,

I hope this email finds you well. I've been following your Instagram account and I must say, your passion for photography and travel is truly inspiring. As a retired history teacher, I appreciate your interest in exploring different cultures.

I wanted to share with you a traditional Chinese recipe that I think you might enjoy. It's a simple dish called 'Xiaolongbao' (soup dumplings) that originated in Shanghai, my hometown. I've included a recipe below, and I hope you'll give it a try.

Ingredients:
* 2 cups all-purpose flour
* 2 tablespoons cornstarch
* 1/4 cup warm water
* 1/4 cup pork filling (see below)
* 1/4 cup chopped scallions
* 1/4 cup grated ginger
* Salt and pepper to taste

Pork Filling:
* 1 pound ground pork
* 1/4 cup chopped cabbage
* 1/4 cup chopped scallions
* 2 cloves garlic, minced
* 1 tablespoon soy sauce
* 1 tablespoon sesame oil

Instructions:
1. Mix the flour, cornstarch, and warm water to form a dough.
2. Divide the dough into small balls.
3. Roll out each ball into a thin circle.
4. Place a tablespoon of pork filling in the center of each circle.
5. Fold the dough over the filling and seal the edges.
6. Steam the dumplings for 10-15 minutes.

I hope you enjoy this recipe, Astrid. Please let me know if you have any questions or if you'd like any variations.

Best regards,
Jianhua Wang

emails.subject: A Traditional Shanghainese Recipe for You to Try
emails.content:
Dear Astrid,

I hope this email finds you well. I've been following your Instagram account, and I must say, your photography skills are impressive! As a retired teacher, I appreciate the creativity and attention to detail you bring to your posts.

I wanted to share with you a traditional Shanghainese recipe that I think you might enjoy. It's a simple dish called 'Lion's Head Meatballs,' and it's a favorite among locals here in Shanghai. I've included the recipe below, along with some tips on how to prepare it.

Ingredients:
* 500g ground pork
* 1/2 cup chopped scallions
* 1/4 cup grated ginger
* 2 cloves garlic, minced
* 1 tablespoon soy sauce
* 1 tablespoon Shaoxing wine
* 1 tablespoon cornstarch
* Salt and pepper to taste

Instructions:
1. Mix all the ingredients together until just combined. Be careful not to overmix.
2. Use your hands to shape the mixture into small meatballs.
3. Heat some oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat. When the oil is hot, add the meatballs and cook until browned on all sides.
4. Serve with steamed rice and your favorite vegetables.

I hope you enjoy this recipe, Astrid! Let me know if you have any questions or if you'd like any variations on this dish.

Best regards,
Jianhua Wong
